UML Relationship
Arrow Notation
Meaning
When to Use?
Example
Association
A --> B
Class A has a reference to Class B (Field, Method Parameter)
When one class “uses” another as a dependency
UserService --> UserRepository
Bidirectional Association
A -- B
Both A & B refer to each other (No clear ownership)
When two classes depend on each other
Customer -- Product
Aggregation
A o-- B
A contains B, but B can exist independently
When B is a part of A, but not strongly coupled
Company o-- Employee
Composition
A *-- B
A owns B, and B cannot exist without A
When B is tightly coupled with A
Car *-- Engine
Dependency
A ..> B
A temporarily depends on B (Method Parameter, Local Variable)
When A only needs B for a short time
Controller ..> DTO
Inheritance (Generalization)
`A <
– B`
B inherits from A (Extends a Class)
When one class extends another
Interface Implementation (Realization)
`A <
.. B`
B implements interface A
When a class implements an interface
